caption.text:
[AYD FAMILIES] 
So, let me introduce them, they're 2 little girls from South Korea. 
They're Gabriella and Ceicilia.
I think they're the youngest delegation, because they said to me that they're 15 years old in Korea (it means 14 years old in Indonesia).
Look at their expression, so cute and childish right? üòÇüòÑ
.
I don't have sister in my family, so i never feel being a big brother to sister (you don't say?!).
And when i met them, i feel like they're my sister... (just in different families and country) .
There are two Indonesian sentences that they always speak to me "Saya Gadis Baik" & "Saya Cinta Kamu". I wanted to reply in Korean, but i can't, so i reply in english "Yes, you're good girls" :))
.
Actually, they're the people that i miss the most! 
In the last AYD night, they were so sad because their delegation will depart earlier from Jogja. So we had met in the final mass and i cried a lot :"
.
Save the "Blangkon" from me okeeyy...
When i go to Korea, you must wear it hahaha
I promise we will meet again, i don't know when, but you have my words :))
Safe trip to Korea!!
